This paper discusses a method for efficient hand pose estimation on embedded devices, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques for joint position estimation and robotics (RO) applications for AR/VR wearables. The paper also discusses the network architecture and training procedure, which involves machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Finally, the paper mentions the use of depth sensors, which are commonly used in multimedia (MM) applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.MM.
